  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attack was executed through a single malicious transaction (0xb5cfa4ae4d6e459ba285fec7f31caf8885e2285a0b4ff62f66b43e280c947216) by an attacker-controlled address (0x69fa61eb4dc4e07263d401b01ed1cfceb599dab8) on the Arbitrum network. The attacker leveraged price manipulation techniques to exploit LavaLending's oracle dependency. By artificially distorting the price feeds of one or more assets used within the protocol, the attacker was able to manipulate collateral valuations. This allowed them to either over-borrow against undercollateralized positions or liquidate positions at artificially favorable rates, ultimately draining approximately $130K in value from the protocol. The attack pattern is consistent with classic oracle manipulation exploits seen across DeFi lending platforms.",
